00:00:12.547 --> 00:00:14.281 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
So, even with One-Shot Kill.

00:00:14.414 --> 00:00:17.652 position:19% line:83% align:start
We still couldn't beat
Miss Hundred Faces.

00:00:17.785 --> 00:00:19.954 position:44% line:83% align:start
Yeah,
I should've expected that.

00:00:20.454 --> 00:00:22.222 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Doesn't look good
for us, does it?

00:00:22.557 --> 00:00:23.591 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:00:24.792 --> 00:00:26.059 position:38% line:89% align:start
Saionji?

00:00:31.766 --> 00:00:33.267 position:38% line:89% align:start
You know?

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:34.969 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm kinda surprised you're not
freaking out right now.

00:00:35.537 --> 00:00:37.070 position:10% line:89% align:start
I could say the same to you.

00:00:37.304 --> 00:00:39.941 position:38% line:83% align:start
Uh. What?
No way, not this girl.

00:00:40.207 --> 00:00:41.441 position:33% line:89% align:start
[both sighs]

00:00:42.844 --> 00:00:43.878 position:38% line:89% align:start
You know.

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:45.212 position:16% line:89% align:start
Now that you're with me,

00:00:45.345 --> 00:00:46.480 position:27% line:83% align:start
there's something
that I have to say.

00:00:46.614 --> 00:00:49.249 position:44% line:83% align:start
Huh?
Why do you sound so serious?

00:00:49.884 --> 00:00:51.019 position:38% line:89% align:start
Saionji.

00:00:51.318 --> 00:00:53.688 position:24% line:83% align:start
Shinohara, please,
my heart isn't ready yet!

00:00:54.388 --> 00:00:56.524 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've got a meeting
so you'll need to hide.

00:00:57.124 --> 00:00:58.358 position:41% line:89% align:start
Pardon?

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:05.934 position:16% line:83% align:start
All right, team. It seems
our all-out war was a bust.

00:01:06.668 --> 00:01:09.571 position:16% line:83% align:start
As things stand, directly
defeating Tsumugi Shiina,

00:01:09.737 --> 00:01:11.773 position:24% line:83% align:start
Miss Hundred Faces,
is impossible.

00:01:12.774 --> 00:01:15.175 position:21% line:83% align:start
So what, are we like,
just supposed to give up?

00:01:15.309 --> 00:01:16.644 position:30% line:89% align:start
Absolutely not.

00:01:17.011 --> 00:01:19.747 position:7% line:83% align:start
If our enemy's willing to play
fast and loose, so will we.

00:01:20.147 --> 00:01:21.649 position:7% line:89% align:start
Whatever it takes, we'll do it.

00:01:21.916 --> 00:01:24.484 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SHINJI] You say that,
but we're still outmatched.

00:01:24.919 --> 00:01:27.055 position:13% line:83% align:start
She's got complete control
of this game.

00:01:27.321 --> 00:01:29.089 position:10% line:89% align:start
Right, so we start a new one.

00:01:29.591 --> 00:01:31.191 position:13% line:89% align:start
Set it up inside of ASTRAL.

00:01:31.325 --> 00:01:32.594 position:30% line:89% align:start
One final game.

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:33.795 position:44% line:83% align:start
[ALL]
Huh?

00:01:34.494 --> 00:01:36.631 position:13% line:83% align:start
It would appear you've been
preparing for this,

00:01:36.764 --> 00:01:37.699 position:24% line:89% align:start
that's commendable.

00:01:37.966 --> 00:01:40.068 position:24% line:83% align:start
But we'd still have
to convince her to play.

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:41.435 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's true.

00:01:41.636 --> 00:01:43.236 position:24% line:83% align:start
Miss Hundred Faces
holds the majority

00:01:43.370 --> 00:01:44.639 position:24% line:89% align:start
of the area by far.

00:01:44.772 --> 00:01:46.608 position:30% line:83% align:start
If she can win
just by waiting it out,

00:01:46.741 --> 00:01:48.475 position:35% line:83% align:start
why bother
playing another game?

00:01:48.910 --> 00:01:50.745 position:19% line:83% align:start
And with tomorrow being
the last day,

00:01:50.878 --> 00:01:53.113 position:27% line:83% align:start
Kurahashi'll try
to dig his heels in deep.

00:01:53.313 --> 00:01:55.783 position:44% line:83% align:start
Yeah.
He won't stay out of this,

00:01:55.984 --> 00:01:57.351 position:19% line:89% align:start
which ultimately means

00:01:57.484 --> 00:01:59.954 position:16% line:83% align:start
we're facing off against
two opponents, not one.

00:02:00.888 --> 00:02:03.891 position:33% line:83% align:start
Knowing that.
Are you willing to trust me?

00:02:04.559 --> 00:02:06.060 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Yes.
-No question!

00:02:06.193 --> 00:02:07.160 position:35% line:89% align:start
Of course.

00:02:07.294 --> 00:02:08.663 position:35% line:83% align:start
[chuckles]
I guess so.

00:02:08.796 --> 00:02:10.064 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:02:10.464 --> 00:02:12.499 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hmm. I'm counting on you.

00:02:13.101 --> 00:02:14.535 position:7% line:89% align:start
We only have one shot at this.

00:02:14.702 --> 00:02:16.604 position:30% line:83% align:start
Let's show 'em
what we're made of!

00:02:17.005 --> 00:02:18.338 position:35% line:83% align:start
-All right!
-Right!

00:02:19.439 --> 00:02:20.775 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroto sighs]

00:02:21.843 --> 00:02:25.245 position:13% line:83% align:start
Now then, how do I convince
Shiina to play a game?

00:02:25.412 --> 00:02:27.247 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI]
Finally! There you are!

00:02:27.849 --> 00:02:29.149 position:38% line:89% align:start
Big bro!

00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:30.785 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
A surprise attack?

00:02:31.019 --> 00:02:32.620 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Ah.
-Hey!

00:02:32.787 --> 00:02:35.355 position:19% line:83% align:start
Let's play some games!
Wha'dya say?

00:02:35.623 --> 00:02:36.658 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:02:38.526 --> 00:02:40.227 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI]
Seriously? I lost again?

00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:41.194 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
She's behaving as though

00:02:41.328 --> 00:02:42.897 position:16% line:89% align:start
yesterday never happened.

00:02:43.631 --> 00:02:46.901 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hey. You are genuinely
Miss Hundred Faces, aren't you?

00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:48.670 position:30% line:89% align:start
Huh? Of course!

00:02:48.803 --> 00:02:52.073 position:7% line:83% align:start
Bona fide participating member
of Seijo Academy!

00:02:52.305 --> 00:02:53.373 position:13% line:89% align:start
How'd you wind up becoming

00:02:53.508 --> 00:02:54.976 position:16% line:83% align:start
involved in all of this,
anyway?

00:02:55.109 --> 00:02:56.644 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hmm? How, you ask?

00:02:59.814 --> 00:03:01.582 position:16% line:83% align:start
Well, I don't really like
going to school,

00:03:01.716 --> 00:03:03.751 position:19% line:83% align:start
so more often than not,
I just stay home playing games

00:03:03.885 --> 00:03:05.753 position:30% line:83% align:start
and doing stuff
on the computer.

00:03:06.353 --> 00:03:08.255 position:38% line:83% align:start
Oh, yeah,
you've said that before.

00:03:08.623 --> 00:03:10.058 position:16% line:89% align:start
I got into middle school

00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:12.527 position:10% line:83% align:start
and thought I'd be done with
mandatory education soon,

00:03:12.694 --> 00:03:14.327 position:21% line:83% align:start
that I wouldn't have
to deal with dull classes

00:03:14.461 --> 00:03:16.164 position:13% line:89% align:start
and dumb teachers anymore.

00:03:16.396 --> 00:03:17.497 position:21% line:89% align:start
But then, it hit me!

00:03:17.632 --> 00:03:18.966 position:30% line:83% align:start
If I didn't get
into high school,

00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.069 position:30% line:83% align:start
I couldn't play
the cool star-catching game!

00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:22.870 position:44% line:83% align:start
Okay.
I guess you're right.

00:03:23.004 --> 00:03:24.872 position:10% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI] There was no way I
was gonna miss out on something

00:03:25.006 --> 00:03:27.075 position:21% line:83% align:start
that was actually fun
for a change.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:28.543 position:7% line:89% align:start
So I modded my Device a little

00:03:28.676 --> 00:03:30.410 position:24% line:83% align:start
and force-installed
a special program

00:03:30.545 --> 00:03:31.746 position:24% line:89% align:start
that'd let me play!

00:03:32.180 --> 00:03:34.314 position:7% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] The first fake account
in Academy Island history

00:03:34.448 --> 00:03:36.150 position:7% line:89% align:start
was a boredom-alleviating whim?

00:03:36.283 --> 00:03:37.819 position:38% line:83% align:start
[giggles]
Impressed?

00:03:38.452 --> 00:03:40.555 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yeah, real impressed.

00:03:40.922 --> 00:03:42.222 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:03:42.990 --> 00:03:45.358 position:24% line:83% align:start
But then, one day,
I got this weird message

00:03:45.492 --> 00:03:47.695 position:33% line:83% align:start
from a person
called Mikado-something.

00:03:47.862 --> 00:03:48.796 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm?

00:03:48.930 --> 00:03:51.231 position:16% line:83% align:start
He wanted me to join him
and was all like

00:03:51.364 --> 00:03:53.433 position:33% line:83% align:start
"Your talents
would serve me well."

00:03:54.068 --> 00:03:55.570 position:7% line:89% align:start
It was some super shady stuff!

00:03:55.770 --> 00:03:59.040 position:10% line:83% align:start
I mean, really! That's pretty
much evil organization 101!

00:03:59.507 --> 00:04:02.076 position:10% line:83% align:start
Anyway, that's who invited me
to join ASTRAL.

00:04:02.210 --> 00:04:03.410 position:10% line:89% align:start
He then gave me this OP Star

00:04:03.544 --> 00:04:05.813 position:27% line:83% align:start
that lets me make
perfect copies of things.

00:04:06.279 --> 00:04:07.682 position:33% line:83% align:start
In exchange,
all he asked me to do

00:04:07.815 --> 00:04:09.817 position:38% line:83% align:start
was issue
a proclamation of war.

00:04:10.051 --> 00:04:11.619 position:16% line:83% align:start
The one where I declared
I was gonna defeat

00:04:11.753 --> 00:04:13.788 position:7% line:89% align:start
you and the Empress, remember?

00:04:14.188 --> 00:04:15.223 position:38% line:89% align:start
Vividly.

00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:16.958 position:16% line:89% align:start
So that's what happened.

00:04:17.225 --> 00:04:18.258 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:04:18.893 --> 00:04:22.130 position:13% line:83% align:start
[sighs] Tomorrow's gonna be
ASTRAL's grand finale,

00:04:22.362 --> 00:04:23.731 position:38% line:89% align:start
isn't it?

00:04:23.998 --> 00:04:26.433 position:13% line:83% align:start
The last day I get to play
with everyone at the event.

00:04:26.901 --> 00:04:28.035 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm so excited,

00:04:28.169 --> 00:04:32.372 position:24% line:83% align:start
I don't think that
I can sleep a single wink.

00:04:32.974 --> 00:04:34.542 position:24% line:89% align:start
She says, sleeping.

00:04:35.576 --> 00:04:36.811 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Sweet little Shiina.

00:04:37.044 --> 00:04:38.445 position:33% line:83% align:start
She probably
doesn't have a clue

00:04:38.579 --> 00:04:40.081 position:10% line:89% align:start
what's really at stake here.

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:41.783 position:16% line:89% align:start
She's just playing along.

00:04:43.518 --> 00:04:46.220 position:21% line:83% align:start
Victory would be fun,
and defeat disappointing.

00:04:46.687 --> 00:04:48.856 position:35% line:83% align:start
In the end,
it's all just a game to her.

00:04:51.192 --> 00:04:52.994 position:7% line:89% align:start
Still, she's not gonna give up.

00:04:53.326 --> 00:04:56.097 position:7% line:83% align:start
She'll keep on playing the game
until somebody wins.

00:04:56.731 --> 00:04:59.499 position:7% line:83% align:start
Somehow, I have to convince her
that she's already lost.

00:04:59.734 --> 00:05:02.804 position:21% line:83% align:start
That the game's over,
and it's finally time to stop.

00:05:13.247 --> 00:05:15.716 position:21% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] And so, the
three surviving ASTRAL players

00:05:15.850 --> 00:05:17.819 position:27% line:83% align:start
gathered together
on the game field.

00:05:18.385 --> 00:05:19.520 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

00:05:19.654 --> 00:05:21.789 position:44% line:83% align:start
Hey.
I've been thinking, Shiina.

00:05:22.223 --> 00:05:23.257 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:05:23.658 --> 00:05:25.726 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm Miss Hundred Faces
right now, silly.

00:05:26.227 --> 00:05:28.663 position:19% line:83% align:start
But wouldn't you rather
end this thing as yourself?

00:05:28.930 --> 00:05:31.464 position:13% line:83% align:start
Show everyone who's really
been playing all this time?

00:05:31.966 --> 00:05:32.867 position:33% line:89% align:start
You think so?

00:05:33.134 --> 00:05:35.636 position:30% line:83% align:start
Fine. I suppose
the Empress act can wait.

00:05:37.038 --> 00:05:38.673 position:19% line:89% align:start
There! Happy, Big Bro?

00:05:39.040 --> 00:05:40.174 position:35% line:89% align:start
"Big bro?"

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.577 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Oh, crap! Oh, and Shiina.

00:05:42.910 --> 00:05:44.979 position:19% line:83% align:start
Since this is the first
we're meeting on the field,

00:05:45.246 --> 00:05:47.715 position:33% line:83% align:start
I think maybe
we should go over the rules.

00:05:47.882 --> 00:05:48.816 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:50.518 position:33% line:83% align:start
As of today,
only three academies

00:05:50.651 --> 00:05:52.220 position:33% line:83% align:start
still remain
in the competition.

00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:54.989 position:19% line:83% align:start
Those are Ouka, Eimei,
and Seijo.

00:05:55.723 --> 00:05:57.191 position:7% line:89% align:start
But of the surviving finalists,

00:05:57.325 --> 00:05:58.726 position:7% line:89% align:start
I have the most captured area,

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:01.329 position:16% line:83% align:start
the most spells, and the
highest support rating, too!

00:06:01.629 --> 00:06:02.663 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
You sure do.

00:06:03.130 --> 00:06:04.665 position:16% line:83% align:start
But aren't you forgetting
something?

00:06:04.799 --> 00:06:05.533 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:06:05.666 --> 00:06:07.034 position:10% line:89% align:start
Before this contest started,

00:06:07.168 --> 00:06:09.369 position:19% line:83% align:start
you issued a challenge
to Saionji, didn't you?

00:06:10.071 --> 00:06:11.939 position:16% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] You declared war
on her through ITube

00:06:12.073 --> 00:06:14.407 position:30% line:83% align:start
with the whole
of Academy Island watching.

00:06:15.309 --> 00:06:17.678 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh. Guess I did do that.

00:06:17.945 --> 00:06:19.714 position:10% line:83% align:start
You haven't forgotten the win
condition of the game

00:06:19.847 --> 00:06:21.448 position:19% line:83% align:start
you challenged her to,
have you?

00:06:21.682 --> 00:06:23.351 position:35% line:83% align:start
It was kind
of an important point.

00:06:23.684 --> 00:06:25.586 position:24% line:83% align:start
I think it was that
whoever beats you first

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:27.521 position:21% line:83% align:start
-would be the winner.
-That's right.

00:06:28.289 --> 00:06:30.558 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, basically that means
our ranks in ASTRAL

00:06:30.691 --> 00:06:32.226 position:10% line:89% align:start
have no real bearing at all.

00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:35.062 position:33% line:83% align:start
I recall you
saying something else, too.

00:06:35.296 --> 00:06:37.565 position:19% line:83% align:start
That if neither of you
could actually beat me,

00:06:37.698 --> 00:06:39.033 position:33% line:83% align:start
then I myself
would be considered

00:06:39.166 --> 00:06:40.935 position:35% line:83% align:start
the victor
of the Empress battle.

00:06:42.136 --> 00:06:43.204 position:16% line:89% align:start
If it came down to that,

00:06:43.337 --> 00:06:44.471 position:30% line:83% align:start
then you agreed
to let me decide

00:06:44.605 --> 00:06:45.840 position:27% line:83% align:start
what would happen
to you afterwards.

00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.809 position:44% line:83% align:start
Huh?
Did I actually say all of that?

00:06:49.377 --> 00:06:51.312 position:13% line:89% align:start
Ah. It does sound familiar.

00:06:51.545 --> 00:06:54.414 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yeah. Which means in the fight
for the name of "Empress",

00:06:54.649 --> 00:06:57.018 position:19% line:83% align:start
I could technically win
just by running away.

00:06:57.551 --> 00:06:58.886 position:16% line:89% align:start
Honestly, on that front,

00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:00.554 position:16% line:83% align:start
there's no real incentive
for me to fight you.

00:07:00.755 --> 00:07:02.023 position:24% line:89% align:start
But if I did that,

00:07:02.290 --> 00:07:03.791 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'd inevitably lose in ASTRAL.

00:07:04.191 --> 00:07:06.127 position:24% line:83% align:start
The same holds true
for Saionji.

00:07:06.761 --> 00:07:07.929 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm not relinquishing

00:07:08.062 --> 00:07:09.496 position:21% line:83% align:start
the throne of Empress
to you, kid.

00:07:09.664 --> 00:07:11.065 position:13% line:89% align:start
A part of me wouldn't mind

00:07:11.198 --> 00:07:13.433 position:10% line:83% align:start
Shinohara playing it evasive
while the clock ran out.

00:07:14.001 --> 00:07:15.002 position:35% line:89% align:start
That said.

00:07:15.236 --> 00:07:16.436 position:21% line:89% align:start
If you do win ASTRAL,

00:07:16.570 --> 00:07:17.772 position:27% line:83% align:start
then Ouka Academy
would drop down

00:07:17.905 --> 00:07:19.607 position:41% line:83% align:start
in rank
to at least sixth place.

00:07:20.174 --> 00:07:22.076 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's not something
I can accept.

00:07:22.543 --> 00:07:23.644 position:27% line:89% align:start
So then. Shiina,

00:07:24.145 --> 00:07:26.881 position:16% line:83% align:start
what's say we settle this
with a new game instead?

00:07:27.014 --> 00:07:27.982 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm?

00:07:28.115 --> 00:07:30.051 position:30% line:83% align:start
You understand
what I just said, right?

00:07:30.584 --> 00:07:32.186 position:21% line:89% align:start
ASTRAL isn't enough.

00:07:32.687 --> 00:07:36.057 position:16% line:89% align:start
It isn't? Well, uh, okay.

00:07:36.324 --> 00:07:37.558 position:38% line:83% align:start
[smiles]
So then,

00:07:37.692 --> 00:07:39.627 position:38% line:83% align:start
how about
we play winner-take-all

00:07:40.027 --> 00:07:41.829 position:27% line:83% align:start
with another game
called "Crossboard?"

00:07:42.229 --> 00:07:45.399 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's a turn-based board game
that works inside ASTRAL.

00:07:45.766 --> 00:07:47.802 position:13% line:83% align:start
If you're able to beat me,
both the competition

00:07:47.935 --> 00:07:49.837 position:16% line:83% align:start
and the title of Empress
belong to you.

00:07:50.338 --> 00:07:53.341 position:19% line:83% align:start
On our end, it gives us
a reason to stand and fight.

00:07:53.607 --> 00:07:56.043 position:13% line:83% align:start
